
# Path Curl Generator

A tool to generate curl API calls and comment the full request path including the base URL.

## Installation

```bash
# Install from the current directory
pip install -e .
```

## Usage

### As a Python Module

```python
from src.path_curl_generator import generate_curl_command

curl_command = generate_curl_command(
    base_url="https://api.example.com",
    path="/v1/users",
    method="POST",
    headers={"Authorization": "Bearer token123"},
    data={"name": "John Doe", "email": "john@example.com"}
)

print(curl_command)
```

### From the Command Line

```bash
# Basic usage
python main.py https://api.example.com /v1/users

# With HTTP method and headers
python main.py https://api.example.com /v1/users -X POST -H "Authorization: Bearer token123"

# With JSON data
python main.py https://api.example.com /v1/users -X POST -j '{"name": "John Doe", "email": "john@example.com"}'

# With query parameters
python main.py https://api.example.com /v1/users -p "page=1" -p "limit=10"
```

## Example Output

```
# Full request path breakdown:
# Base URL: https://api.example.com
# Path: /v1/users
# Complete URL: https://api.example.com/v1/users

curl -X POST \
  -H 'Authorization: Bearer token123' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"name": "John Doe", "email": "john@example.com"}' \
  'https://api.example.com/v1/users'
```

## Running Tests

```bash
python -m unittest discover tests
```
